<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 6:25AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
Tazewell County through 700 AM EDT...
At 625 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Raven, or near Richlands, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Richlands...
Tazewell...
Cedar Bluff...
Burkes Garden...
Raven...
Amonate...
and Gratton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
